#### Wizengamot

* We know there are about 50 members at Harry's trial,[^20210329-4] when it sits
  in a "full criminal trial"[^20210329-6] or in other words, "the full
  court."[^20210329-7]
* We do not know if "the full court" is the same as "the full Wizengamot," it is
  possible that some subset is on a "Judicial Committee" or
  some-such.[^20210329-8]
* We know that, at least when sitting as a court, Mr. Weasley is not allowed
  in.[^20210329-9]
* We know that, at least when sitting as a court, Mr. Malfoy is not allowed
  in.[^20210329-10]
* It is strongly implied that the Malfoy family does in fact have a title from
  the norman conquest.[^20210330-2]
* We are told that a Potter "has twice sat on the Wizengamot"[^20210330-1]
* There exists a "British Youth Representative to the Wizengamot"[^20210329-11]
* We know that the Wizengamot has a Charter of Rights.[^20210329-5] This
  suggests, but does not prove, a legislative function. 
* Able to at least suggest that a Minister leave office.[^20210330-9]

